canonical:
  title: 何處秋深好
  author: 金時習
  language: lzh
  text: 何處秋深好漁村八九家淸霜明柿葉綠水漾蘆花曲曲竹籬下斜斜苔徑賖西風一釣艇歸去逐烟霞何處秋深好秋深隱士家新詩題落葉夕飡掇籬花木脫千峯瘦苔斑一路賖道書堆玉案瞋目對朝霞何處秋深好秋深商旅家石橋留月色楓樹染霜花孤舘三年夢離亭十里賖關山何處是遙望隔雲霞
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 何處秋深好
  author: 金時習
  language: lzh
  text: 何處秋深好。漁村八九家。淸霜明柿葉。綠水漾蘆花。曲曲竹籬下。斜斜苔徑賖。西風一釣艇。歸去逐烟霞。何處秋深好。秋深隱士家。新詩題落葉。夕飡掇籬花。木脫千峯瘦。苔斑一路賖。道書堆玉案。瞋目對朝霞。何處秋深好。秋深商旅家。石橋留月色。楓樹染霜花。孤舘三年夢。離亭十里賖。關山何處是。遙望隔雲霞。
korean:
  title: 하처 추심호
  author: 김시습
  language: kor
  text: |-
    그 어떤 곳이 가을 깊어 좋은가
    고기잡이 마을에 8ㆍ9 집 있다
    맑은 서리는 감나무 잎을 밝히고
    푸른 물결은 갈대꽃에 출렁인다
    구불구불한 대 울타리 그 밑에
    비뚤비뚤한 이끼 길이 멀어라
    서쪽 바람에 낚싯배 한 척
    연기와 놀을 따라 돌아가더라
    그 어떤 곳이 가을 깊어 좋은가
    가을이 깊은 은사의 집이어라
    새로 얻은 시는 낙엽에 적고
    저녁 먹고는 울타리 꽃 모은다
    나뭇잎 떨어지매 봉마다 여위었고
    이끼 아롱진 한 갈래 길이 멀도다
    도서를 옥책상에 쌓아 두고는
    성난 눈으로 아침 놀을 바라본다
    그 어떤 곳이 가을 깊어 좋은가
    가을이 깊은 장삿집 여관이어라
    돌다리에는 달빛이 잠자는데
    단풍나무는 서리꽃에 물들었다
    외로운 여관에서 3년의 꿈이
    떠나는 술자리에 10리가 멀다
    관산은 그 어느 곳에 있는가
    구름과 놀 넘어를 멀리 바라본다
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_1420_010_0420&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Where Does Autumn Run Deep?
  author: Kim Si習
  language: eng
  text: |-
    Where does autumn run deep and fair?
    In a fishing village of eight or nine homes,
    Clear frost brightens the persimmon leaves,
    Green waters ripple with reed flowers.
    Beneath the winding bamboo fence,
    A moss-covered path stretches long and far.
    One fishing boat on the western wind—
    Following smoke and clouds, it returns.

    Where does autumn run deep and fair?
    In the hermit's dwelling, autumn runs deep.
    New verses inscribed on falling leaves,
    After evening's meal, gathering fence flowers.
    When the trees shed their leaves, each peak grows lean,
    Moss-mottled, a single path stretches far.
    Tome upon tome stacked on the jade desk,
    Furrowed brow gazing at the morning glow.

    Where does autumn run deep and fair?
    In the merchant's inn, autumn runs deep.
    On the stone bridge, moonlight sleeps,
    Maple trees dyed in frost's white flowers.
    Three years of dreaming in the lonely inn,
    Ten miles at the parting feast, how distant.
    Where lies the frontier of mountains and passes?
    Beyond clouds and mist, gazing far.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: Kim Si습(1435-1493) was a renowned Korean poet and scholar of the Joseon period, known for his classical Chinese poetry and literary contributions to the Dongmunseon.
  - key: ''
    value: 'This poem presents three contrasting visions of autumn''s beauty: the fisherman''s simple life, the hermit''s scholarly retreat, and the merchant''s wandering loneliness, each revealing different aspects of the human condition.'
  - key: ''
    value: The repeated refrain 'Where does autumn run deep and fair?' frames each stanza as a meditation on finding meaning and peace within life's different circumstances.
